author: Frank Torres
title: Buddy Dyer casts vote in Orlando Mayor race
text:
Buddy Dyer casts vote in Orlando Mayor race October 26, 2015 Pinterest 0 
Orlando Mayor Buddy Dyer was at the Orange County Supervisor of Elections office on Monday afternoon to cast his vote in his bid for a fourth term. 
Accompanied by a group of Veterans, Dyer entered the building, then met with friends and supporters before taking a few questions from the media. 
“It’s important to get out and vote early, just in case you can’t make it on November 3rd” said Dyer “It looks like we’re going to have a low voter turnout and your vote is going to count event more.” 
The other two candidates running against Dyer had a presence in the area as well. Educator Sunshine Linda Grund was there and said she wanted to meet with Supervisor of Election Bill Cowles to ensure all of the rules were being followed. 
“I hope people are out there voting. I’ve offered myself as a candidate. I just need citizens to show up and have their voices heard in this election” Grund stated. 
Businessman and Veteran Paul Paulson also had over a dozen sign waivers rallying across the street, but none were authorized to speak to the media. 
The limited polling that is available in the race has Dyer up approximately 20 points, however with the limited turnout, none of the candidates are taking anything for granted. 
“We’re going to continue to communicate and encourage people to turn out. I feel very good about our message and the only danger we have is if people feel complacent and think it’s already in the bag. We need to have people actually vote to have it in the bag.” said Dyer in closing. Readers who read this, also read these
